The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Briefs

 Calcutta 

 High Court on Tuesday asked police commissioner Prasun Mukherjee 

 to find out whether the angel atop the Victoria Memorial has 

 stopped swirling because of sabotage. The division bench of 

 Justice P.K. Samanta and Justice T. Sen also asked the authorities 

 to file a report stating how far it had complied with the 

 recommendations of a panel for the monuments upkeep. 

 Chief 

 minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee will unveil an airconditioned 

 photo archive at Writers Buildings on Wednesday. The government 

 has spent over Rs 9 lakh on the archive. 

 A 

 25-year-old man was found dead with his throat slit and private 

 parts mutilated in Sonarpur on Tuesday. 

 Traffic 

 sergeant Sovon Dutta caught a youth near North Port police 

 station while he was fleeing with a taxi from Jadavpur on 

 Monday night. The taxi belongs to Sanjib Roy. 

 SSKM 

 Hospital has been facing a water crisis since last week, as 

 its deep tubewell is not working. The PWD has not undertaken 

 repairs. The Calcutta Municipal Corporation is sending water 

 tankers to the hospital. 




